ariant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">above). There might be a paragraph or a list</span></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><font style="font-size: 14px;">of items..so on.</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">When you apply the CSS’s “</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">float</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">” property on the first </span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">&lt;div&gt;</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> tag of your </span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">HTML</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> page, it does </span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">it does nothing ( or behaves like a default HTML). However, it is important to use the “</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">float</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">”</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">so second </span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">&lt;div&gt;</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> in your page to work. </span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">The CSS “</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">float</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">” tries to put the div tags (boxes) in sequences depend on how you apply ( left or </span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">right ). </span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">If a HTML page size  is smaller than the total size of the div boxes, it will dynamically put a </span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">&lt;dev&gt;</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"> tag</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">•</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">on the next line.</span></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><font style="font-size: 14px;">- If the &lt;div&gt; tag does not have a floating property, it will try to follow the block or &lt;div&gt; which has no the floating property.</font></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><font style="font-size: 14px;">  That’s why usually the footer try get afiter the header doing all kind of nasty things ( if there were &lt;div&gt;’s with left or right</font></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><font style="font-size: 14px;">  floats set).</font></span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Clear Fix Code</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">/* Clear Float Code */</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">.clearfix</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">:after {</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">content</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">: ".";</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">display</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">: </span><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 143, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">block</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">height</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">: </span><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 143, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">0</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; f